.\" LINUX(1) Manual Page
.TH LINUX 1 "May 6, 2026" "C-SCHOOL" "Linux Manual"
.SH NAME
linux \\- Linux operating system mastery
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linux
[topic]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Covers all aspects of the Linux operating system from kernel to shell.
.SH TOPICS
.TP
.B 001_Filesystem
File hierarchy, permissions, and navigation
.TP
.B 002_Shell_Basics
Bash fundamentals and scripting  
.TP
.B 003_System_Admin
Users, services, and process management
.TP
.B 004_Networking
Network configuration and tools
.TP
.B 005_Package_Management
apt, yum, dnf, pacman usage
.TP
.B 006_Kernel_Concepts
Kernel internals and modules
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B pwd
Print working directory.
.TP
.B ls [-la]
List directory contents.
.TP
.B cd [dir]
Change directory.
.TP
.B chmod [perms]
Change file permissions.
.TP
.B chown [user]
Change file owner.
.TP
.B ps [-aux]
List processes.
.TP
.B top
System monitor.
.TP
.B systemctl [command]
Service manager.
.TP
.B ip [a]
Network configuration.
.SH FILESYSTEM
.TP
.B /bin
Essential command binaries.
.TP
.B /usr
User programs.
.TP
.B /etc
Configuration files.
.TP
.B /var
Variable data (logs, cache).
.TP
.B /home
User home directories.
.TP
.B /root
Root user home.
.SH SEE ALSO
vim(1), bash(1), man(7)